      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(docker): add optional Claude CLI install and persistent ~/.claude directory",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen running OpenClaw in Docker with `anthropic/*` providers configured to\nuse Claude Code (Claude Max/Pro subscription), the `@anthropic-ai/claude-code`\nCLI is not installed in the container image. Users must manually rebuild the\nimage or exec into the container to install it. The `~/.claude` OAuth\ncredential directory is also not created/persisted across container upgrades.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Add optional `OPENCLAW_INSTALL_CLAUDE_CLI` build arg that installs\n  `@anthropic-ai/claude-code` globally via npm when set (opt-in, no size\n  impact for default builds)\n- Create `~/.claude` directory in the Docker image with correct ownership\n  so OAuth credentials survive container upgrades when backed by a volume\n\n## Evidence\n\nBuild verification: `docker build --build-arg OPENCLAW_INSTALL_CLAUDE_CLI=1 .`\ncompletes successfully. The default build (without the arg) is unaffected.\n\n**Label**: enhancement\n\n_AI-assisted._",
